description:
liminal spaces and args too lol


In this video, we explore Wendigoon Arg, a remote location in Northern Ontario that is known for its spectacular analog horror. This liminal space is home to some of the most iconic and terrifying horror movies of all time, We'll talk about the history of Wendigoon Arg, the unique atmosphere and the role that horror movies have played in shaping our culture. This is one video you don't want to miss! Welcome to my channel, i love analog horror, and I'm here to bring you the best in liminal spaces, Wendigoon arg, and all things Lovecraftian. Subscribe if you like what you see, and feel free to share the videos with your friends!In this video, I'm sharing my love of analog horror with you. From Wendigoon Arg to Liminal Spaces, I'll be highlighting some of my favorite analog horror movies.If you're a fan of horror movies, then I hope you'll join me in this exploration of analog horror. From frightful movies to creepy galleries, I'll be sharing some of my favorite horror movies with you. So dive in and let's explore some of the scariest places on earth in the comfort of your own home!and

comments.text:
I think what is scary about horror in general is when something is wrong, but there's "wrong" like, hearing soft music at night, discovering your mom bloodied on the floor of the kitchen, noticing everyone on Earth is gone, or even just waking up in the middle of the night with two unblinking eyes staring at you from the corner of the room; and then there's "wrong" like, the toaster is broken, you missed the bus, your friend caught the flu and didn't come to school, or you saw a squirrel today.

I think the latter is kinda what a lot of horror feels like nowadays, but worse. Not just analog even horror movies feel like that, because there's a following of codes that we've had for horror for decades and basically haven't changed, which makes everything mundane and predictable despite the "wrong" situation. How many times have you seen the "violin getting more high pitched as main character looks behind him, sees nothing, music stops, goes back to his original position and some creature jumpscares him from the front"? That's also why people believe mascot horror games are dead because it's all the same fucking thing. The wrong stops being wrong if the genre you base it on always used the same wrongs. To the viewer, the wrong then just becomes unimpressive.
comments.author: @Tom_Katsu_pz
